{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1994 |Team=Texas A&M Aggies |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Southwest Conference |Division= |ShortConference=SWC |CoachRank= |APRank=8 |Record=10-0-1 |ConfRecord=6-0-1 |HeadCoach=[[R.C. Slocum]] |StadiumArena=[[Kyle Field]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{1994 Southwest Conference football standings}} The '''1994 [[Texas A&M Aggies]] football team''' completed the season with a 10-0-1 record. The Aggies had a regular season [[Southwest Conference]] record of 6-0-1. Their record was good enough to win the Southwest Conference, but they were ineligible for the postseason due to probation.
